Company Profile:If a picture speaks a
thousand words, a video speaks 25,000 words in a second. Vertigo Pictures began when 2 kindred souls, Mark Pestana &
Elvin Chuwa, decided to form a production house that would allow them to collaborate
full-time on ideas & concepts they had discussed over the years as friends
& colleagues.Their
mission for Vertigo Pictures would be to produce work that is always fresh,
exciting, surprising & relevant. Vertigo Pictures would be recognized for
its strength in content, originality & innovation.Today,
Vertigo Pictures is a full-fledged Singaporean film & television production
company that produces a variety of material ranging from documentaries to
television commercials & corporate films.
Job Description:TranscribingBasic editiingBasic administrationPresentation pitchesAttending production meetings;Typing, editing, copying and distributing scripts;Typing and distributing schedules, or call sheets;Assisting cast members, Running errandsRunning errands between the production office and other departments;Making schedules, shot lists, logs and other paperwork for post-production.All of which will be under mentorship by a Producer or Production Manager.
